data.title: Roger Daltrey
data.meta_description: ROGER DALTREY. Lead singer with legendary english mod-rock band first formed in 1964 who grew to be considered one of the greatest and most influential ever in popular music. They rose to fame with a pioneering and exciting live stage instrument destruction show and a series of classic Top 10 singles, including one of the decades defining rock anthems "My Generation". Their now legendary hellraising drummer Keith Moon died of a drug overdose in his sleep in 1978 and was replaced by Small Faces drummer Kenney Jones. Bassist John Entwistle died of a heart attack in Las Vegas in 2002. The groups two original remaining members (Roger Daltrey & Pete Townsend) continue to record and perform to high acclaim .........
data.text: ROGER DALTREY. Lead singer with legendary english mod-rock band first formed in 1964 who grew to be considered one of the greatest and most influential ever in popular music. They rose to fame with a pioneering and exciting live stage instrument destruction show and a series of classic Top 10 singles, including one of the decades defining rock anthems "My Generation". Their now legendary hellraising drummer Keith Moon died of a drug overdose in his sleep in 1978 and was replaced by Small Faces drummer Kenney Jones. Bassist John Entwistle died of a heart attack in Las Vegas in 2002. The groups two original remaining members (Roger Daltrey & Pete Townsend) continue to record and perform to high acclaim .........
